    "faq_Ld7yCC": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "item_7kpVea": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the top speed of the Yozma IN 10 Pro?",
            "content": "<p>The top speed reaches 20km/h delivering powerful acceleration for both urban commuting and short leisure rides.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_fcVKfM": {
          "type": "item",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "How many riding modes are available?",
            "content": "<p>IN 10 Pro offers three speed modes (approx. <strong>22 MPH</strong>, <strong>34 MPH</strong>, and <strong>47 MPH</strong>) to suit different riding preferences.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_UrTPVR": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What rider height is the IN 10 Pro suitable for?",
            "content": "<p>The IN10 Pro is suitable for riders between 4.7 ft and 6.3 ft in height and is recommended for users aged 14 years and above.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_kjznVh": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How long does it take to fully charge the battery?",
            "content": "<p>With the 60V 5A US standard charger (XLR head), a full charge takes about 6–7 hours.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_LezKXa": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What type of motor does it use?",
            "content": "<p>IN 10 Pro features a 5500W mid-drive motor for superior power delivery and climbing ability compared to hub motors.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_D6ew6a": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the battery specification? Is it removable?",
            "content": "<p>It comes with a 60V 27AH lithium battery that’s removable for convenient charging and maintenance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_UGrEGQ": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Safety Instructions —— Important Tips",
            "content": "<p>1. Wear Proper Protective Gear</p><p>Always wear an approved helmet when riding. Protective gear such as goggles, gloves, elbow and knee pads, and long pants is strongly recommended. Wear lace-up shoes with rubber soles. Do not ride barefoot, in open-toed shoes, or in high heels.</p><p>2. Ride Only in Safe and Legal Areas</p><p>Do not ride on highways, indoors, on slopes exceeding 30°, or on uneven, slippery, or unfamiliar terrain. Beginners should practice in an open area before riding in public spaces.</p><p>3. Operate Responsibly to Minimize Risk</p><p>Always hold the handlebars with both hands and avoid high-risk maneuvers. Do not ride under the influence of alcohol, medication, or when unwell. Obey local traffic laws and yield to pedestrians and other road users.</p><p>4. Battery Safety and Handling</p><p>Do not store batteries in environments above 70°F (21°C) or below 32°F (0°C). Batteries must be disposed of in accordance with local regulations. Do not throw batteries into fire or dispose of them with household waste.</p><p>5. Observe Weight and Weather Limits</p><p>Maximum load is 120 kg. The recommended rider weight is approximately 80 kg. Do not ride in rain, storms, fog, or other extreme weather conditions. Avoid water exposure to the motorcycle and battery.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
